Package uk.ac.leeds.ccg.agdt.generic.util

Class Generic_Time

java.lang.Object
uk.ac.leeds.ccg.agdt.generic.util.Generic_Time
public class Generic_Time
extends java.lang.Object
This predates java.time. It was developed for dynamic models that ticked through time. It has methods to help process dates and times and to aggregate data by these. It should not be confused with the identically named Generic_Time class.
Version:
1.0.0
Author:
Andy Turner

      public static int getMonth​(java.lang.String month, java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> month3Letters)
      In the case where month3Letters is from getMonths3Letters() and month is "January" or "Jan" or "Janu" (etc.) then this will return 1.
      Parameters:
      month - A month e.g. "January" for which the index of a three letter version + 1 is returned.
      month3Letters - For example see getMonths3Letters().
      Returns:
      An int represent the month Jan = 1, Dec = 12.

    • getMonth3Letters

      public static java.lang.String getMonth3Letters​(int monthNumber)
      Parameters:
      monthNumber - expected values 1 to 12 inclusive.
      Returns:
      "Jan" for monthNumber = 1, ..., "Dec" for monthNumber = 12. For any other value null is returned.

    • getMonthNumber

      public static java.lang.String getMonthNumber​(java.lang.String month3Letters)
      Parameters:
      month3Letters - Expecting "Jan", to "Dec".
      Returns:
      For month3Letters "Jan" return "01", ..., month3Letters "Dec" return "12". For non recognised month3Letters return null.

    • getMonthInt

      public static int getMonthInt​(java.lang.String month3Letters)
      Parameters:
      month3Letters - Expecting "Jan", ..., "Dec".
      Returns:
      1 if month3Letters is "Jan", ..., 12 if month3Letters is "Dec" and -1 otherwise.
